What is one of the most important markers (in my opinion) of success in homeschooling, or parenting for that matter? My answer may or may not surprise you 😉 #homeschoolingbyheart 

If you’d like me to share more of my thoughts on this in another reel, let me know in the comments 😘🤗

Cover pic: my beautiful daughter in law and newest grand babe ❤️

We want to be parents that our adult children will want to spend time with. That relationship building starts now while they’re home with you.

Highlight #1 from my experience: If you want teenagers that will talk to you (or adult children for that matter) then develop the habit of listening with interest and respect right now. Yes, even if they are only 3 yes old 😉

Did I do this perfectly? Not even. But it was always in the forefront of my mind. #homeschoolingbyheart

The story isn’t over once they graduate. Take comfort in that. You are not responsible for every dash and dot in your children’s lives. He who began a good work in them will be faithful to finish it. #homeschoolingbyheart
You are enough. He makes us able 🙏🏻 # jesus #homeschoolingbyheart

What will make your homeschool sustainable? After 3 decades of homeschooling this is my heartfelt belief. 

I’m not able to maintain this page like I used to, but my heart for homeschooling & encouraging mamas in this decision is unwavering. One way I can do that on a deeper level is to spend one-on-one time with some of you.

I’m going to offer a few mentoring calls again if you’d like to have some real heart to heart encouragement. In the past my calls have been $75 for an hour, this time around they’ll be $50.
Message me here or at @toniweber if you’d like to know more. I’d love to connect with you 🤗❤️

Babies need nature too. Include them in the exploring, the beauty seeking, the treasure finding. They are naturally so curious and in wonder of it all—what a joy. What a joy shared! I believe that cultivating a love and respect of God’s creation is one of the most valuable things you can instill while raising your family. Not just by studying it, but by being in it as much as possible. 

This is nana life- sharing that same joy now with my grandkids. The “Birdy Cam” is something my daughter @hannah.chillingworth started and it’s our favorite way to see the world right now, through her eyes. I’m sharing more Birdy Cam moments in my stories. #homeschoolingbyheart

Accepting this was a significant turning point for me. We can believe that we alone steer the ship of our children’s lives, what a weight that can be. It was one that had me sinking at times. But that is not the truth. God never intended for us to bear a burden that heavy. 

Share this with a friend 🤗

Photo: @overlandunderbudget 💕

These years of raising a family are priceless. You won’t ever regret breaking free from outside pressure and expectations of what learning should look like. You get to decide what your homeschool will look like. You get to create a family culture of life and learning all your own 🙌 #homeschoolingbyheart

Are you being driven or led?
.
The former is brought on by fears and worry. By outside pressures or standards that tell you constantly that you’re not doing enough, the kids aren’t measuring up. That if you don’t keep your nose to the grindstone it will all fall apart.
.
The latter starts from a place of peace. The kind of peace that the Lord gives. That peace will constantly tell you that He has a plan that you can trust. It will guide your days without pressures and fears, and it will reaffirm you that you are enough. Just keep your eyes on Him, and not on the pressures that want to suck you in. #homeschoolingbyheart

This has the power to make a huge change in your day to day experience. It did for me! 
#homeschoolingbyheart
Are you padding your days with enough margin, or are things getting smashed together and crossing that red line? #homeschoolingbyheart

This is what I would tell you when you’re having a really hard day, week or season. We can put so much value on getting the school work done. Checking those boxes. Flipping those pages.

For me, the absolute treasure in homeschooling is relationship. Hours upon hours of time I would have never gotten if my kids went away to school.
Hours upon hours that compounded over the years and added up to what me and their dad have now with them. What they have with each other. 

The funny thing that we can loose sight of is how quickly they can absorb and learn things. And that they also don’t need to “know” everything.

You will never regret missing some assignments, re arranging your plans, or setting aside all “school work” to give extra attention to strengthening those heart strings. However, regret over not making it a priority is guaranteed.

{{ I’ve recently opened up my mentor calls again and I’m enjoying them so much. I love spending an hour of one-on-one time with mamas, offering guidance & encouragement. Homeschooling is a walk of faith, but not one you ever walk alone 🙏🏻 If you think a call might be of help to you, send me a message or email me. Let’s connect! }}

Patience. Quiet determination. Focus. 

So much of life needs this for us to reach our goals, especially when you’re homeschooling and raising a family. 

These are thoughts that came to me while I was drawing this owl (slide to see) It was a slow and tedious process, it couldn’t be rushed. Every detail needed my focus. 

Mama- have faith that even your tiny steps forward are the precious bricks of what you’re building—

A family culture. Learning that brings life. Protecting sacred childhood. Relationship and connection. Faith, values, character. And joy!! A home filled with it 🎉

Brick by brick. Day by day.

Don’t let discouragement stop you because you can’t raise a wall in a day. Every brick you lay down is moving you closer. God is filling in the gaps with his mortar. He’s creating something so beautiful—you need to trust him. You need to believe that he holds the plans and you can be led each day for what’s needed next 🌟#homeschoolingbyheart 

pic: my son and granddaughter 🥰
Follow my art journey @toniweber

Don’t bog yourself down with systems and methods created for the masses. Use your creative freedom to infuse a life-giving experience. Not just for learning, but for the happy longevity of your homeschool.

You have been your child’s teacher from day one. That does not need to change when they reach school age because you don’t hold a degree or haven’t been specifically trained. You are the expert on your own children. You are not only capable, but the most natural fit. Don’t doubt that powerful mama heart of yours to help your children well in all things—even in their schooling. There’s no match for it out there.

Did you sign up for my free group mentor call? Link in my stories 🤗

Pic: me and grand-baby #4

Every smile, every moment of eye contact, each little kiss and spontaneous hug— your gentle answers, kind patience, and humble apologies—all of it, noticed or not, is building a bond and a fortress that will stand.

Even when you fall short, you rise again. You embrace your children and tie your heart to theirs with your actions of faithfulness. Over and over you are there. Each day, each year, quietly plowing and planting seeds.

Your harvest is taking shape, little tastes of it are already evident. One day it will be fully ripe and not just for a season—but for the rest of your life.

Wishing all of you a very happy Mother’s Day! xox

We know the importance of speaking words of life to our children, but do you speak them over yourself?

I’m going to be opening my free group mentoring call this Saturday with why affirming ourselves as mothers and individuals is crucial. The truth & power of these words comes from God, not from ourselves. When we lean into who he says we are, we become empowered beyond what anything in this world can offer us.

My call happens this Saturday morning at 9:30! DM me to get on the list! 

📸 me and the grand babes 🐥

A mother’s affirmation I wrote for you ❤️

“God has blessed me with my children, and I am equipped to love them and provide for them. 

God makes me able to meet their needs and leads me to the right decisions concerning them. 

His grace is with me and will fill in all the gaps. When I make mistakes, his faithfulness never wavers towards me or my children. 

He continues to work all things for our good in spite of my shortcomings. I am a joyful mother because the Lord gives me strength and I am filled with his spirit!”

Share this with your mama friends and give them a truth-boost for their day 🤗
